TRANSCRIPTION_TRANSLATION.translation: My child is constantly arguing. What to do? First of all, understand that they have a need to feel worthy, that they will survive, and thus compete to have the last word. In order to help the child, we must both satisfy the need and teach communication skills, but only by our own example. So, we must calm down ourselves, and even if the child says something we do not agree with, we should say, I cannot agree with that. But at the same time, let's observe for now, read, think about it more, and we will talk about it later. Similarly, often reinforce if the child asks us questions, saying, it is so pleasant for us, it is so pleasant for me, when you are interested in my opinion, and say that we are pleased that the child agreed with something. Over time, the child will learn.
